article.description: Oklahoma snapped a 12-game losing streak against Big 12 competition Tuesday night by beating Texas Tech 83-74.
article.headline: Oklahoma tops Texas Tech to end Big 12 skid
article.linkText: Oklahoma tops Texas Tech to end Big 12 skid
article.story: NORMAN, Okla. -- Cade Davis matched his career high with 25 points, Andrew Fitzgerald scored 20 and Oklahoma snapped a 12-game losing streak against Big 12 competition Tuesday night by beating Texas Tech 83-74. Davis missed his first four 3-point attempts but went 4-for-4 when it mattered the most as the Sooners (9-9, 1-3) prevailed in a meeting of the last two teams without a conference win. Davis hit two 3-pointers during a 10-2 run as Oklahoma pulled away early in the second half after the Red Raiders (8-11, 0-4) got within three. John Roberson led Texas Tech with 21 points and Brad Reese scored 15. The Red Raiders tied their season-high with 20 turnovers to squander a season-best 16 offensive rebounds.
